1. Nmap (Network Scanning & Enumeration)

Used to discover hosts, open ports, and services.

## 2. Wireshark (Packet Analysis)

Used to capture and analyze network traffic.

## 3. Burp Suite (Web Application Testing)

Used for intercepting and modifying HTTP/HTTPS requests.

##4. SQLmap (SQL Injection Automation)

Used to detect and exploit SQL injection vulnerabilities.

## 5. Gobuster (Directory/File Brute-forcing)

Used to find hidden directories and files on web servers.

## 6. Dirsearch (Web Content Discovery)

Alternative to Gobuster with more features.

## 7. Hydra (Password Cracking / Brute Force)

Used for brute-forcing login credentials.

## 8. John the Ripper (Password Cracking)

Used to crack hashed passwords.

## 9. Hashcat (Advanced Password Cracking)

GPU-based password cracking tool.

## 10. Steghide (Steganography – Data Hiding)

Used to hide/extract data inside images.

## 11. Binwalk (File Carving & Analysis)

Used to detect and extract embedded files.

## 12. Strings (Data Extraction)

Used to extract readable text from binaries.

## 13. Grep (Pattern Searching)

Used to search for patterns like flags or credentials.

## 14. Netcat (nc) (Networking Utility)

Used for banner grabbing, reverse shells, and connections.

## 15. OpenSSL (SSL/TLS Analysis)

Used to inspect certificates and encrypted connections.

## 16. SSH (Remote Access)

Used to securely connect to remote machines.

